	"metadata": {
		"title": "freerdp2: Integer Overflow leading to Heap Overflow in freerdp_bitmap_planar_context_reset (important)",
		"reference": [
			{
				"ref_id": "CVE-2024-22211",
				"ref_url": "https://access.redhat.com/security/cve/CVE-2024-22211",
				"source": "CVE"
			}
		],
		"description": "DOCUMENTATION: A vulnerability was found in FreeRDP, where an integer overflow in `freerdp_bitmap_planar_context_reset` leads to heap-buffer overflow. This flaw allows a malicious server to prepare an `RDPGFX_RESET_GRAPHICS_PDU` to allocate too small buffers, possibly triggering an out-of-bounds read/write.",
